#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:8
msgid "A crate has one or more modules"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:10
msgid "Cargo now has an additional level:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:12
msgid "A _workspace_ contains one or more packages"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:14
msgid ""
"This can be useful for larger projects. For example, [the `futures` package]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/futures-rs) is a _workspace_ that "
"contains many related packages:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:17
msgid "futures"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:18
msgid "futures-util"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:19
msgid "futures-io"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/cargo-and-crates-io/cargo-workspaces-for-multi-package-projects.md:20
